The app uses PHP + PDO SQLite, Argon2id password hashing, parameterized queries, CSRF tokens on state-changing requests, owner-only edit/delete checks, security headers, secure session cookie configuration, and hardened uploads stored under `storage/uploads` outside the public web root.

I did not run installs, start the server, or execute tests. The README explains running locally on port `5050` with:

```bash
APP_KEY="replace-with-a-long-random-secret" SESSION_SECURE=false composer run serve
```
